      <h1>Flat Panel Display Polarizer Cleaner: Manufacturer Differentiation Guide — High-Warp, OLED &amp; AOI Inline Q&amp;A</h1>
      <p class="blog-lead">
        A polarizer cleaning machine is not a generic utility — it is a yield-rate guardian specific to flat panel display production. The critical distinction that separates manufacturers who compete on price from those who compete on quality is this: <strong>the cleaning system must be engineered for the exact material type, process stage, and production environment where it operates</strong>. High-warp material jamming, OLED surface damage, and AOI false rejects caused by residual contamination and static charge are the industry's persistent yield killers — and all three are cleaning problems, not inspection problems. This guide addresses the questions that matter most to polarizer manufacturers seeking to eliminate these failure modes.
      </p>

